%20pay%20to%20have%20their%20food%20delivered%20can%20be%20hefty.%20A%20study%20from%20FinanceBuzz%20in%20January%20found%20that%20orders%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-postmates-food-delivery-costs-twice-as-much-as-pickup-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%20and%20Chick-fil-A%20can%20cost%20twice%20as%20much%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20delivery%20services%20like%20DoorDash%20and%20Postmates%20as%20they%20would%20at%20the%20restaurant%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20might%20make%20delivery%20seem%20like%20an%20obvious%20place%20for%20consumers%20to%20cut%20back%20their%20spending%20these%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20delivery%20companies%20say%20that's%20not%20actually%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20DoorDash%20and%20Uber%20reported%20earnings%20this%20summer%20that%20surpassed%20analysts'%20expectations%20%E2%80%94%20and%20showed%20that%20lots%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-doordash-instacart-still-delivering-lots-as-consumers-pull-back-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20are%20still%20willing%20to%20pay%20for%20delivery%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20being%20more%20thrifty%20in%20other%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20really%20strong%20demand%20on%20the%20consumer%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20DoorDash%20CEO%20Tony%20Xu%20said%20on%20the%20company's%20earnings%20call%20in%20August.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20actually%20seeing%20some%20of%20the%20challenges%20that%20you%20may%20be%20hearing%20about%20or%20reading%20about%20in%20other%20headlines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoorDash%20customers%20have%20continued%20ordering%20food%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20increasingly%2C%20groceries%20and%20other%20products%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20service%2C%20Xu%20said.%20Both%20DoorDash%20and%20Uber%20Eats%20have%20also%20seen%20growth%20in%20their%20subscription%20programs%2C%20which%20come%20with%20a%20monthly%20fee%20but%2