u-kashmir-permanent%2Farticleshow%2F113148727.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Swiss%20city%20cut%20red%20tape%20and%20ended%20up%20with%20many%20more%20homes.%20It's%20a%20model%20for%20the%20US.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20house%20and%20an%20apartment%20building%20with%20price%20tags%20on%20them%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66db4b7da0ff598b266578f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKamala%20Harris%20says%20she%20wants%20to%20'cut%20red%20tape'%20to%20boost%20the%20housing%20supply%20and%20reduce%20costs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThere's%20new%20evidence%20out%20of%20Zurich%20that%20reducing%20restrictions%20on%20housing%20construction%20boosts%20supply.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20upzoning%20is%20a%20long-term%20solution%20that's%20necessary%2C%20but%20not%20sufficient%2C%20to%20address%20the%20crisis.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20her%20housing%20policy%20agenda%2C%20Democratic%20presidential%20nominee%20Kamala%20Harris%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-kamala-harris-plans-to-build-3-million-new-homes-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epromised%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bcut%20red%20tape%20and%20needless%20bureaucracy%26quot%3B%20to%20build%20millions%20of%20additional%20homes%20and%20bring%20down%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEconomists%20and%20urban%20planners%20say%20that%20to%20make%20housing%20more%20abundant%20and%20affordable%2C%20we%20need%20to%20loosen%20zoning%20regulations%20in%20many%20neighborhoods%20and%20legalize%20the%20construction%20of%20denser%2C%20taller%20housing%2C%20such%20as%20duplexes%2C%20townhomes%2C%20and%20apartment%20buildings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20countries%20have%20already%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZurich%2C%20Switzerland%20offers%20the%20latest%20model.%20As%20a%20small%2C%20mountainous%20country%20with%20limited%20buildable%20land%20and%20high%20demand%2C%20Switzerland%20has%20long%20been%20sensitive%20to%20urban%20sprawl.%20Starting%20in%20the%20mid-1990s%2C%20Swiss%20citizens%20voted%20to%20densify%20various%20parts%20of%20the%20Canton%20of%20Zurich%2C%20one%20of%20the%20country's%2026%20states%20and%20home%20to%20its%20biggest%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Apartment%20buildings%20are%20pictured%20behind%20farm%20houses%20in%20Affoltern%2C%20just%20outside%20Z%C3%BCrich.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ce21e3c72ebc54a40f5de6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22837%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EApartment%20buildings%20behind%20farm%20houses%20in%20Affoltern%2C%20just%20outside%20Zurich%2C%20Switzerland.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Buholzer%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20canton%20didn't%20uniformly%20alter%20its%20zoning%20laws.%20The%20citizens%20of%20each%20municipality%20voted%20on%20various%20proposals%20to%20%26quot%3Bupzone%26quot%3B%20or%20allow%20more%20housing%20units%20by%20loosening%20zoning%20restrictions.%20The%20process%20was%20slow%20and%20staggered%2C%20and%20the%20average%20upzoning%20was%20quite%20incremental%20%E2%80%94%20think%20of%20a%20home%20with%20three%20floors%20that%20can%20add%20one%20extra%20floor.%20Much%20of%20the%20rezoning%20took%20place%20in%20neighborhoods%20surrounding%20Zurich's%20medieval%20city%20center%2C%20which%20is%20protected%20by%20historic%20preservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty-five%20years%20into%20this%20process%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0094119024000597%23sec2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20study%20by%20Swiss%20researchers%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20found%20that%20upzoning%20boosted%20living%20space%20and%20housing%20units%20by%20a%20significant%20amount%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0about%209%25%20in%20the%20subsequent%20five%20to%2010%20years%20%E2%80%94%20while%20keeping%20rent%20growth%20under%20control.%20The%20study%20found%20that%20areas%20that%20were%20hungriest%20for%20new%20housing%20were%20the%20most%20responsive%20to%20the%20policy%20changes.%20Areas%20with%20high%20demand%2C%20evidenced%20by%20high%20rents%20and%20home%20prices%20and%20already%20constrained%20by%20limits%20on%20housing%2C%20saw%20the%20most%20new%20construction.%20And%20the%20more%20density%20allowed%2C%20the%20more%20impactful%20the%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20study's%20key%20findings%20is%2C%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20upzone%2C%20upzone%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Simon%20B%C3%BCchler%2C%20coauthor%20of%20the%20study%20and%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20finance%20at%20Miami%20University.%20%26quot%3BGive%20people%20the%20incentive%20to%20build.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20provides%20more%20evidence%20that%20supply%20and%20demand%20can%20be%20harnessed%20to%20keep%20housing%20prices%20in%20check.%20Another%20example%20comes%20from%20New%20Zealand%2C%20where%20Auckland's%20upzoning%20measures%20legalizing%20the%20construction%20of%20medium-density%20housing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-lower-rents-home-prices-build-more-houses-new-zealand-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslowed%20down%20skyrocketing%20housing%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw29440%2Fw29440.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20study%20of%20S%C3%A3o%20Paulo's%20upzoning%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20similarly%20positive%20impacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZurich%20shows%20that%20upzoning%20is%20necessary%20but%20not%20sufficient.%20Allowing%20for%20more%20housing%20boosts%20affordability%2C%20but%20it%20takes%20time.%20There%20are%20a%20slew%20of%20other%20necessary%20fixes%20to%20bring%20housing%20costs%20down%20%E2%80%94%20from%20building-code%20changes%20to%20long-term%20expansion%20of%20services%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20amenities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20think%20they're%20going%20to%20upzone%20and%20they're%20going%20to%20solve%20the%20affordability%20crisis%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20years.%20They're%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20B%C3%BCchler%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20long-term%20solution%2C%20but%20it%20is%20a%20solution%20that's%20necessary%20and%20that%20works.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Homes%20in%20the%20town%20of%20K%C3%BCsnacht%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20Lake%20Zurich%20in%20Switzerland.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ce20e543b5e59d16b5b19d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22696%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHomes%20in%20the%20town%20of%20K%C3%BCsnacht%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20Lake%20Zurich%20in%20Switzerland.%3Cp%3EChristian%20Hartmann%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d4a990d-dceb-46a3-a92c-5f7d590f5db3%5C%22%3EKnee-capping%20NIMBYism%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20elements%20of%20Swiss%20law%20and%20society%20that%20make%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20more%20welcoming%20to%20development%20and%20resistant%20to%20NIMBYism%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BNot%20In%20My%20Backyard%26quot%3B%20anti-development%20sentiment%2C%20that%20cripples%20so%20much%20new%20construction%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20most%20American%20cities%2C%20Zurich%20is%20a%20society%20of%20renters%20rather%20than%20homeowners.%20More%20than%2070%25%20of%20households%20are%20tenants.%20While%20property%20owners%20are%20incentivized%20to%20oppose%20additional%20housing%20in%20their%20neighborhoods%20that%20would%20boost%20supply%20and%20depress%20their%20home%20values%2C%20renters%20tend%20to%20be%20much%20more%20supportive%20of%20development%20that%20keeps%20rents%20affordable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20helps%20that%20European%20cities%20are%20generally%20more%20accomodating%20of%20higher-density%20living.%20A%20whopping%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fdca3f034-bfe8-4f21-bcdc-2b274053f0b5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E64%25%20of%20Swiss%20residents%20live%20in%20apartments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20compared%20to%20just%2028%25%20of%20US%20residents%2C%20and%20the%20country%20also%20has%20an%20especially%20comprehensive%20and%20well-connected%20public%20transportation%20network.%20While%20Zurich's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zh.ch%2Fde%2Fsoziales%2Fbevoelkerungszahlen.html%3Fkeyword%3Deinwohner%23%2Fhome%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epopulation%20has%20grown%20significantly%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20last%20quarter%20century%2C%20European%20cities%20tend%20to%20have%20more%20restrictive%20immigration%20laws%20than%20their%20counterparts%20in%20Canada%2C%20the%20US%2C%20and%20New%20Zealand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20evidence%20from%20Europe%20is%20important%20as%20it%20shows%20that%20upzoning%20can%20increase%20supply%20even%20in%20places%20where%20density%20is%20relatively%20more%20common%20and%20accepted%2C%20and%20overseas%20migration%20is%20less%20of%20a%20factor%2C%26quot%3B%20Matthew%20Maltman%2C%20an%20Australian%20economist%20who's%20closely%20studied%20New%20Zealand's%20housing%20reforms%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20certainty%20around%20how%20regulations%20function%20in%20Zurich%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20in%20the%20US%20or%20New%20Zealand%2C%20which%20include%20more%20veto%20points%20in%20the%20building%20process%2C%20Maltman%20said.%20While%20developers%20can't%20apply%20to%20local%20authorities%20to%20bypass%20zoning%20regulations%2C%20local%20residents%20also%20can't%20lobby%20to%20stop%20a%20project%20from%20happening%20if%20it%20abides%20by%20the%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20government%20level%2C%20municipalities%20are%20incentivized%20to%20welcome%20new%20residents%20because%20they%20disproportionately%20rely%20on%20income%20taxes%20for%20revenue%2C%20B%C3%BCchler%20noted.%20Property%20taxes%20in%20Switzerland%20are%20very%20low%2C%20so%20the%20more%20density%20a%20city%20or%20town%20allows%2C%20the%20more%20income%20tax%20they%20can%20collect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EB%C3%BCchler%20plans%20to%20investigate%20how%20rent%20changes%20in%20Zurich%20compare%20with%20other%20parts%20of%20Switzerland%20to%20get%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20the%20price%20impacts%20of%20upzoning.%20Ideally%2C%20deregulating%20zoning%20would%20bring%20prices%20down.%20But%20B%C3%BCchler%20considers%20it%20a%20win%20that%20rents%20were%20unchanged%20in%20Zurich%2C%20when%20adjusted%20for%20housing%20quality%2C%20even%20as%20the%20canton's%20population%20and%20demand%20for%20housing%20grew.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20upzoning%20didn't%20help.%20What%20it%20means%20is%20that%20without%20the%20upzoning%2C%20we%20would%20have%20seen%20even%20more%20rent%20increases%20than%20what%20we've%20seen%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZurich's%20example%20is%20crucial%20in%20informing%20policy%20change%20in%20places%20like%20the%20US%20because%20real-world%20evidence%20of%20the%20effects%20of%20upzoning%20can%20help%20convince%20governments%20and%20voters%20to%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEconomists%20have%20argued%20the%20case%20for%20zoning%20reform%20based%20upon%20other%20evidence%20%E2%80%94%20usually%20based%20upon%20economic%20theory%20or%20sophisticated%20economic%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20Maltman%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20can%20be%20easier%20to%20sell%20the%20public%20on%20place%20X%20implemented%20policy%20Y%20and%20it%20had%20Z%20effect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-lower-rent-home-price-increases-build-more-houses-switzerland-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725702122000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66db4b7da0ff598b266578f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-lower-rent-home-price-increases-build-more-houses-switzerland-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22New%20research%20in%20Switzerland%20adds%20to%20the%20international%20literature%20finding%20that%20upzoning%20boosts%20the%20supply%20and%20affordability%20of%20housing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-lower-rent-home-price-increases-build-more-houses-switzerland-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Rohit%20Sharma%20is%20still%20the%20same%20guy%20that%20he%20was%2016%20years%20ago'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725702011000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113148713%2Cimgsize-52426.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnews%2Frohit-sharma-is-still-the-same-guy-that-he-was-16-years-ago%2Farticleshow%2F113148525.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Scott%20Styris%20identified%20Rohit%20Sharma's%20unique%20talent%20during%20their%20time%20together%20at%20Deccan%20Chargers%20in%20IPL%202008%20and%202009.%20Despite%20a%20poor%20start%2C%20the%20team%20won%20the%20championship%20in%202009.%20Rohit%20went%20on%20to%20lead%20Mumbai%20Indians%20to%20five%20IPL%20titles%20and%20guided%20India%20to%20winning%20the%202024%20T20%20World%20Cup%2C%20showcasing%20his%20leadership%20and%20batting%20skills.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnews%2Frohit-sharma-is-still-the-same-guy-that-he-was-16-years-ago%2Farticleshow%2F113148525.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20rare%20move%2C%2