%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVidar%20is%20associated%20with%20the%20god%20of%20vengeance%20in%20Scandinavian%20mythology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThe%20Ukrainian%20military%20began%20using%20the%20Dragon%20drone%2C%20which%20burns%20the%20area%20underneath%20with%20thermite%20%F0%9F%A5%B0%F0%9F%A5%B0%F0%9F%A5%B0%20Thermite%20is%20a%20mixture%20of%20burning%20granules%20of%20iron%20oxide%20and%20aluminum.%20About%20500%20grams%20of%20thermite%20mixture%20can%20be%20placed%20under%20a%20standard%20FPV%20drone.%20The%20chemical%20reaction%20is%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F3XIzc3LLHN%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F3XIzc3LLHN%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Anastasia%20(%40Nastushichek)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNastushichek%2Fstatus%2F1831763026959016265%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%205%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20incendiary%20bombs%20-%20munitions%20that%20are%20designed%20to%20cause%20fire%20-%20has%20brought%20focus%20on%20their%20potential%20use%20on%20civilian%20populations%2C%20and%20establishments%20apart%20from%20the%20military.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussia-ukraine-war-terrifying-video-shows-firebombs-raining-down-in-ukraines-donetsk-3191332%5C%22%3EIn%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Russia%20used%20thermite%20bombs%20over%20the%20eastern%20Ukrainian%20town%20of%20Vuhledar%20after%20the%20defeat%20in%20a%20tank%20battle.%20The%20Russians%20spew%20thermite%20over%20the%20border%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Russians%20reportedly%20used%20122mm%20Grad%209M22S%20rockets%20launched%20from%20the%20Soviet-era%20B-21%20multi-rocket%20launcher%20system%20with%20a%20thermit%20warhead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20videos%20have%20emerged%20where%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20troops%20have%20used%20such%20weapons%20on%20the%20frontline.%20Thermite%2C%20unlike%20conventional%20bombs%20that%20rely%20on%20a%20blast%20effect%2C%20generated%20intense%20heat.%20It%20is%20widely%20used%20in%20welding%20steel%2C%20iron%2C%20and%20railway%20tracks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20widespread%20use%20of%20thermite%20bombs%20increases%20the%20likelihood%20of%20these%20weapons%20being%20deployed%20in%20populated%20areas.%20The%20result%20could%20be%20catastrophic%2C%20with%20horrific%20injuries%20and%20loss%20of%20life%20among%20civilians%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Iain%20Overton%2C%20Executive%20Director%20of%20Action%20on%20Armed%20Violence%20(AOAV)%2C%20a%20British%20advocacy%20group%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIgnition%20of%20thermite%20is%20slow%20and%20it%20requires%20very%20high%20temperature%20to%20ignite.%20These%20temperatures%20cannot%20be%20reached%20with%20conventional%20black%20powder%20fuses%20or%20nitrocellulose%20rods.%20They%20are%20often%20achieved%20by%20Magnesium%20metal%20strips%20that%20are%20used%20as%20fuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUse%20Of%20Incendiary%20Bombs%20In%20The%20Past%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorld%20War%20I%20was%20witness%20to%20incendiary%20weapons%20when%20Germans%20and%20the%20Allied%20troops%20used%20such%20munitions%20against%20their%20adversary.%20The%20American%20Thermite%20Hand%20Grenade%20Mark%20I%20and%20the%20French%20Model%201916%20incendiary%20grenades%20were%20weapons%20used%20during%20World%20War%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Germans%20developed%20B1.3E%2C%201938%2C%20incendiary%20bombs%20just%20before%20World%20War%202.%20The%20Luftwaffe%20(German%20Air%20Force)%20used%20it%20extensively%20to%20bomb%20British%20cities.%20The%20Imperial%20War%20Museum%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BDuring%201940-41%2C%20the%20Luftwaffe%20caused%20serious%20damage%20by%20dropping%20large%20quantities%20of%20incendiary%20bombs%20on%20British%20towns%20and%20cities%2C%20either%20using%20containers%20that%20were%20carried%20on%20bomb%20racks%20and%20released%20to%20open%20at%20a%20predetermined%20point%2C%20or%20from%20very%20large%20containers%20holding%20up%20to%20700%20bombs%20that%20remained%20on%20the%20aircraft.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20German%20B1E%201%20kg%20incendiary%20aircraft%20bomb%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22A%20German%20B1E%201%20kg%20incendiary%20aircraft%20bomb%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fmot8s698_german-b1e-bomb_625x300_07_September_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20German%20B1E%201%20kg%20incendiary%20aircraft%20bomb%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Image%20credit%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22no%20index%2C%20no%20follow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iwm.org.uk%2Fcollections%2Fitem%2Fobject%2F30021484%5C%22%3EImperial%20War%20Museum%20%C2%A9%20IWM%20(MUN%203291)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Allied%20troops%20used%20Napalm%20-%20a%20flammable%20mixture%20of%20gasoline%20and%20a%20gelling%20agent%20-%20for%20bombings%20and%20throwing%20flames.%20The%20US%20used%20Napalm%20to%20target%20Japanese%20cities.%20Almost%2060%25%20of%20Tokyo%20was%20burnt%20during%20the%20Napalm%20bombings.%20It%20has%20been%20massively%20used%20since%20its%20creation%20in%201942.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Vietnam%20War%2C%20the%20use%20of%20Napalm%20and%20The%20Dow%20Chemical%20Company%20which%20produced%20it%2C%20caught%20the%20world's%20attention%20on%20how%20dangerous%20such%20weapons%20when%20unleashed%20on%20civilians%20which%20caused%20severe%20burns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInternational%20Regulations%20On%20Use%20Of%20Incendiary%20Weapons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEfforts%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20incendiary%20weapons%20started%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20notably%20with%20a%20growing%20concern%20over%20the%20use%20of%20napalm.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdisarmament.unoda.org%2Fconvarms%2Fincendiary-weapons%2F%5C%22%3EIn%201972%2C%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%3C%2Fa%3E%20adopted%20a%20resolution%20referring%20to%20incendiary%20weapons%20as%20'a%20category%20of%20arms%20viewed%20with%20horror'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201980%2C%20the%20Convention%20on%20Prohibitions%20or%20Restrictions%20on%20the%20Use%20of%20Certain%20Conventional%20Weapons%20Which%20May%20Be%20Deemed%20to%20Be%20Excessively%20Injurious%20or%20to%20Have%20Indiscriminate%20Effects%20was%20adopted%20with%20the%20aim%20to%20ban%20or%20restrict%20the%20use%20of%20certain%20types%20of%20weapons%20considered%20to%20cause%20unnecessary%20or%20unjustifiable%20suffering%20to%20combatants%20or%20to%20indiscriminately%20affects%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Protocol%20on%20prohibitions%20or%20restrictions%20on%20the%20use%20of%20incendiary%20weapons%20(Protocol%20III)%20aims%20at%20protecting%20civilians%20and%20civilian%20objects%20from%20the%20use%20of%20this%20type%20of%20weapons.%20It%20prohibits%20targeting%20civilians%20and%20restricts%20targeting%20military%20objects%20located%20within%20populated%20areas.%20The%20Protocol%20also%20prohibits%20the%20use%20of%20incendiary%20weapons%20on%20forest%20or%20other%20plants%20unless%20the%20vegetation%20is%20used%20to%20conceal%20military%20objects.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725696420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fnjjti3k_thermite-bomb_625x300_07_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fvideo-ukraines-dragon-drone-rains-molten-metal-on-russian-positions-6510999%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fire%20rained%20on%20Russian-held%20positions%20in%20the%20occupied%20Kharkiv%20region%20when%20Ukrainian%20drones%20dropped%20thermite%20incendiary%20bombs%2C%20burning%20trees%20and%20reportedly%20some%20Russian%20military%20vehicles.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fvideo