22title%22%3A%22Boeing's%20Starliner%20Spaceship%20Returns%20To%20Earth%20Without%20Astronauts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBoeing's%20beleaguered%20Starliner%20returned%20to%20Earth%20from%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS)%20without%20astronauts%20Sunita%20Williams%20and%20Barry%20E%20Wilmore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gumdrop-shaped%20capsule%20landed%20gently%20at%20the%20White%20Sands%20Space%20Harbor%20in%20New%20Mexico%20at%20approximately%200401%20GMT%20(9%3A30%20am)%2C%20its%20descent%20slowed%20by%20parachutes%20and%20cushioned%20by%20airbags%2C%20having%20departed%20the%20ISS%20around%20six%20hours%20earlier.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FStarliner%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Starliner%3C%2Fa%3E%20spacecraft%20is%20back%20on%20Earth.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAt%2012%3A01am%20ET%20Sept.%207%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FBoeingSpace%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40BoeingSpace%3C%2Fa%3E's%20uncrewed%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20landed%20in%20White%20Sands%20Space%20Harbor%2C%20New%20Mexico.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FvTYvgPONVc%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FvTYvgPONVc%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20NASA%20Commercial%20Crew%20(%40Commercial_Crew)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCommercial_Crew%2Fstatus%2F1832269414521016651%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%207%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20delays%2C%20Starliner%20launched%20in%20June%20for%20what%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20roughly%20weeklong%20test%20mission%20--%20a%20final%20shakedown%20before%20it%20could%20be%20certified%20to%20ferry%20crew%20to%20and%20from%20the%20orbital%20laboratory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20unexpected%20thruster%20malfunctions%20and%20helium%20leaks%20on%20its%20way%20up%20derailed%20those%20plans%2C%20and%20NASA%20ultimately%20decided%20it%20was%20safer%20to%20bring%20Butch%20Wilmore%20and%20Suni%20Williams%20back%20on%20a%20rival%20SpaceX%20Crew%20Dragon%20--%20though%20they'll%20have%20to%20wait%20until%20February%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gumdrop-shaped%20capsule%20touched%20down%20softly%20at%20the%20White%20Sands%20Space%20Harbor%20in%20New%20Mexico%20at%20approximately%200401%20GMT%2C%20its%20descent%20slowed%20by%20parachutes%20and%20cushioned%20by%20airbags%2C%20having%20departed%20the%20ISS%20around%20six%20hours%20earlier.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGround%20teams%20reported%20hearing%20sonic%20booms%20as%20it%20streaked%20red%20hot%20across%20the%20night%20sky%2C%20having%20endured%20temperatures%20of%203%2C000%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20(1%2C650%20degrees%20Celsius)%20during%20atmospheric%20reentry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20smooth%2C%20uneventful%20ride%20was%20seen%20as%20critical%20not%20only%20for%20salvaging%20some%20pride%20but%20also%20for%20Boeing's%20prospects%20of%20achieving%20certification%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20century-old%20aerospace%20giant%20had%20carried%20out%20extensive%20ground%20testing%20aimed%20at%20replicating%20the%20technical%20issues%20the%20spaceship%20had%20experienced%20on%20its%20ascent%20and%20devised%20plans%20to%20prevent%20more%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20its%20reputation%20already%20battered%20by%20safety%20concerns%20affecting%20its%20passenger%20jets%2C%20Boeing%20made%20assurances%20in%20public%20and%20in%20private%20that%20it%20could%20be%20trusted%20to%20bring%20the%20astronauts%20home%20--%20an%20assessment%20not%20shared%20by%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoeing%20believed%20in%20the%20model%20that%20they%20had%20created%20that%20tried%20to%20predict%20the%20thruster%20degradation%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20flight%2C%26quot%3B%20Steve%20Stich%2C%20program%20manager%20for%20NASA's%20Commercial%20Crew%20Program%2C%20told%20reporters%20this%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20%26quot%3Bthe%20NASA%20team%2C%20due%20to%20the%20uncertainty%20in%20the%20modeling%2C%20could%20not%20get%20comfortable%20with%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20characterizing%20the%20mood%20during%20meetings%20as%20%26quot%3Btense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Certification%20decisions%20to%20come%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20undocking%2C%20Starliner%20executed%20a%20powerful%20%26quot%3Bbreakout%20burn%26quot%3B%20to%20swiftly%20clear%20it%20from%20the%20station%20and%20prevent%20any%20risk%20of%20collision%20--%20a%20maneuver%20that%20would%20have%20been%20unnecessary%20if%20crew%20were%20aboard%20to%20take%20manual%20control%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20that%2C%20mission%20teams%20conducted%20thorough%20checks%20of%20its%20thrusters%20in%20preparation%20for%20the%20critical%20%26quot%3Bdeorbit%20burn%2C%26quot%3B%20required%20to%20guide%20the%20capsule%20onto%20its%20reentry%20path%20around%2040%20minutes%20before%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20expectations%20were%20high%20that%20Starliner%20would%20stick%20the%20landing%2C%20as%20it%20had%20in%20two%20previous%20uncrewed%20tests%2C%20NASA%20will%20now%20carefully%20review%20all%20aspects%20of%20the%20mission's%20performance%20before%20deciding%20on%20the%20next%20steps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20awarded%20Boeing%20and%20SpaceX%20multibillion-dollar%20contracts%20over%20a%20decade%20ago%20to%20develop%20spacecraft%20to%20taxi%20astronauts%20to%20and%20from%20the%20ISS%2C%20after%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Space%20Shuttle%20program%20left%20the%20US%20space%20agency%20reliant%20on%20Russian%20rockets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20initially%20considered%20the%20underdog%2C%20Elon%20Musk's%20SpaceX%20surged%20ahead%20of%20mighty%20Boeing%2C%20successfully%20flying%20dozens%20of%20astronauts%20since%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Starliner%20program%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20faced%20numerous%20setbacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20during%20its%20first%20uncrewed%20test%20flight%2C%20a%20software%20glitch%20prevented%20the%20capsule%20from%20rendezvousing%20with%20the%20ISS.%20A%20second%20software%20issue%2C%20which%20could%20have%20caused%20a%20catastrophic%20collision%20between%20its%20modules%2C%20was%20caught%20and%20fixed%20just%20in%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20with%20the%20rocket%20poised%20on%20the%20launchpad%20for%20another%20attempt%2C%20blocked%20valves%20forced%20yet%20another%20postponement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20capsule%20finally%20reached%20the%20ISS%20in%20May%202022%20on%20a%20non-crewed%20flight%2C%20but%20further%20issues%2C%20including%20weak%20parachutes%20and%20flammable%20tape%20in%20the%20cabin%20that%20needed%20removal%2C%20delayed%20the%20crewed%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20current%20mission%2C%20astronauts%20Wilmore%20and%20Williams%20had%20been%20strapped%20into%20their%20seats%20and%20ready%20to%20fly%20twice%20before%20last-minute%20%26quot%3Bscrubs%26quot%3B%20due%20to%20technical%20glitches%20sent%20them%20back%20to%20their%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725684660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Frio23ue8_starliner_625x300_07_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fboeings-starliner-spaceship-returns-to-earth-without-astronauts-6509833%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Boeing's%20beleaguered%20Starliner%20returned%20to%20Earth%20from%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS)%20without%20astronauts%20Sunita%20Williams%20and%20Barry%20E%20Wilmore.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fboeings-starliner-spaceship-returns-to-earth-without-astronauts-6509833%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Byju's%20auditor%20BDO%20resigns%20after%20start%20of%20bankruptc